Package com.novartis.opensource.yada.adaptor

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Adaptor
    The abstract Adaptor class is at the root of the package hierarchy.
    FileSystemAdaptor
    An adaptor for reading from and writing to safe, designated directories on the YADA server.
    JDBCAdaptor
    Abstract subclass defining many methods and fields for JDBC functionality including the construction of SQL statements incorporating pagination, filtering, sorting, and total row counts.
    MySQLAdaptor
    For connecting to MySQL databases via JDBC.
    OracleAdaptor
    JDBCAdaptor class for execution of Oracle SQL queries.
    PostgreSQLAdaptor
    For connecting to PostgreSQL databases via JDBC.
    RESTAdaptor
    For connecting to REST endpoints with YADA.
    SOAPAdaptor
    For execution of SOAP requests
    SQLiteAdaptor
    For connecting to MySQL databases via JDBC.
    SQLServerAdaptor
    Early implementation on JDBCAdaptor extension for MSSQLServer.
    VerticaAdaptor
    For connecting to Vertica databases via JDBC.
    YADAAbstractResultSet
    This class enables the instantiation of compatible ResultSet objects when callable statements otherwise return nothing.
    YADAResultSet
    This class exists to enable instantiation of a ResultSet when a callable statement doesn't otherwise return one.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    YADAAdaptorException
    Typically thrown by any Adaptor subclass after catching any processing exception during query prep or execution.
    YADAAdaptorExecutionException
    Typically thrown by any Adaptor subclass after catching any processing exception during query execution.
